President Donald Trump has sent a notice to the Federal Register stating that the national emergency with respect to persons who commit, threaten to commit, or support terrorism, which was declared in Executive Order 13224 on September 23, 2001, is to continue beyond September 23, 2019. The President cites the ongoing crisis of terrorism and the threat of further attacks as the reasons for continuing the national emergency, stating that it poses an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States.